What is SNS in AWS?

Amazon SNS (Simple Notification Service) is a fully managed messaging service that sends messages/notifications to multiple subscribers at once.

Application Alerts

EC2 CPU > 90%
    │
    ▼
CloudWatch → SNS → Email to DevOps team 📧

Can we set on SNS alert on ASG?

Yes! You can set SNS Alerts on ASG (Auto Scaling Group) ✅

ASG Events That Trigger SNS

when we create ASG we get option to enable for SNS

Create Auto Scaling Group
    │
    ▼
Step 5 — Add Notifications (optional)
    │
    ├── SNS Topic     → choose or create topic
    │
    └── Event Types   → all 4 checked by default:
          ✅ Launch
          ✅ Terminate
          ✅ Fail to launch
          ✅ Fail to terminate

In SNS

Step 1 — Create Topic
  my-alerts-topic ✅

Step 2 — Create Subscriptions (who gets notified)
  Subscription 1 → Email    → devops@company.com
  Subscription 2 → SMS      → +91xxxxxxxxxx
  Subscription 3 → Lambda   → my-function
  Subscription 4 → SQS      → my-queue

Step 3 — Publish Message to Topic
  "EC2 instance launched!"
        │
        ▼
  Topic receives message
        │
        ├──→ Email sent to devops@company.com  📧
        ├──→ SMS sent to +91xxxxxxxxxx         💬
        ├──→ Lambda triggered                  ⚡
        └──→ Message added to SQS queue        📦
